                            <comment id="488850" author="JIRAUSER18433" created="Tue, 24 Feb 2026 15:59:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ve talked about removing LUTF outright. It doesn&apos;t have as much traction as sanity-lnet.sh.And the last two LNDs that landed didn&apos;t substantially (if it all) use it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="488847" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 24 Feb 2026 15:53:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was looking at this the other day and I think the issue is the python version. LUTF was originally written to work with both python2 and python3.&#160; Some platforms like RHEL8 that I have only have python3. The python detection code doesn&apos;t work quite right so LUTF ends up not being built. Try&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;export PYTHON_VERSION=3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and see if it builds.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="488837" author="colmstea" created="Tue, 24 Feb 2026 15:09:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;lutf.sh is being installed by Lustre on the test nodes but the lutf subdir is missing which is causing the failures.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I found this in lustre/tests/Makefile.am&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# Build LUTF only if the packages are available
if BUILD_LUTF
SUBDIRS += lutf
endif # BUILD_LUTF &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;should BUILD_LUTF be set in Jenkins? If so, for which jobs/branches?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="433626" author="yujian" created="Fri, 1 Nov 2024 17:17:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The &quot;lutf&quot; test group session has been failing every build on master branch since 02/2023:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions?jobs%5B%5D=lustre-master&amp;amp;test_groups%5B%5D=lutf&amp;amp;start_date=2023-01-01&amp;amp;end_date=2024-10-30&amp;amp;source=test_sessions#redirect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions?jobs%5B%5D=lustre-master&amp;amp;test_groups%5B%5D=lutf&amp;amp;start_date=2023-01-01&amp;amp;end_date=2024-10-30&amp;amp;source=test_sessions#redirect&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="422348" author="pjones" created="Thu, 25 Jul 2024 19:04:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As per discussion on the LWG call today, moving tickets that do not appear to be essential to fix version 2.17. If the fix lands before code freeze we will update the fix version to reflect that but we want to focus on activities on the critical path. Please speak up if you think that this issue definitely needs to be fixed before we could issue a 2.16 release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
